**1 PURPOSE**

The goal of the Snuggle Squadrons app is to deliver educational components together with an enjoyable and captivating virtual pet experience for users. The app lets users take care of and nurture their virtual pets, encouraging empathy and responsibility. Its nostalgic appeal is rooted on the original Snuggle Squadrons virtual pet. Users get entertaining and interactive lessons on the value of routine, empathy, and caring by feeding, playing, and tending to their pet's needs. The app might also have instructional elements like trivia questions or mini games that teach about subjects like responsibility, animal behavior, and pet care. The ultimate goal of the Snuggle Squadrons app is to amuse users while simultaneously engaging and playfully teaching important life lessons.

**General Design:**

The design of my app is vibrant and playful, with colorful illustrations and characters that appeal to children. Images of cute and friendly pets can enhance engagement.

**Intuitive Design:**

The design of my app flows logically from top to bottom, with clear navigation cues such as buttons and icons that are easily recognizable by children. The main functionalities, such as feeding, playing, and caring for the pet, are easily accessible.

**Content Prioritization:**

My app includes only essential interface elements that are relevant to the primary functions of the app. There are no cluttering the interface with unnecessary elements that could overwhelm young users.

**Legible Text Content:**

I made use of clear and simple fonts that is easy for children to read, with a sufficient text size to ensure readability on various screen sizes.

**Make Interface Elements Clearly Visible:**

All the interface elements in my app, such as buttons and icons, are large enough and spaced appropriately to prevent accidental taps or confusion.

**Hand Position Controls:**

The interactive elements within my app are easy reach of children's fingers, considering the typical hand position when holding a mobile device.

**Images:**

The images of pets in my app are appealing and relatable to children. I tried using the same pet to cater to different preferences, such as a cat. I ensured that the images convey emotions and activities that children can easily understand, such as playing, eating, sleeping, and expressing happiness.
